        public java.lang.String getJson()
        Returns this object as a Json string. Converting to JSON if a cached version is not available. Also to prevent potentially large memory allocations on the server this is moved from the S00PacketServerInfo writePacket function As this method is called from the network threads thread safety is important!
        返回:

      • invalidateJson

        public void invalidateJson()
        Invalidates the cached json, causing the next call to getJson to rebuild it. This is needed externally because PlayerCountData.setPlayer's is public.
